	"description": "Breaking into a new industry or role is difficult. Learning a new set of skills\nand getting a job using them is just that, difficult. You could even say it’s \nO(n)² difficult.\n\nNow try competing for that same role in a market saturated with other folks in\nyour same shoes. Most good things in life aren’t easy, but they are worth\nfighting for.\n\nIn my case, my new job gave me a 20% pay increase from my former role as a\nproject manager. And now, I’m also doing work that invigorates me.\n\nI’ve seen a ",
